search], 30 lectures were held which not only review the history of the press during the past six decades, but also illustrate that journalism itself writes history.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aJournalismvCongresses. 0aJournalismzGermanyxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 4aDeutschland (Bundesrepublik) /Geschichte, Politik 1945ff. 4aDeutschland (Bundesrepublik) /Presse. 4aJournalismus. 4aPressefreiheit. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh  aFreedom of the Press.  aGermany (Federal Republic) / History, Politics 1945 ff.  aGermany (Federal Republic) / Press.1 aBohrmann, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBranahl, Udo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaub, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Inka, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuniok, Rüdiger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoebel, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinrich, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmann, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHömberg, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirchhoff, Hans-Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolb, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoszyk, Kurt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramer, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangenbucher, Wolfgang R., econtributor